  "articleBody": "<!-- Page 11 --><article>\n\n\n        <h5 class=\"yellow\">The Four Horsemen of <cite>The Revelation</cite></h5>\n\n          <p>The narrative continues between the rainbow and John.</p>\n\n\n          <h6 class=\"yellow\">first seal: the white horse - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verse 2</h6>\n\n            <header>\n              <p class=\"no-puce\">chapter 6</p>\n            </header>\n\n            <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-6-1\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-6-1\">\n              <ol class=\"doc\">\n                <li value=\"01\">\n                  <p>I saw that the Lamb opened one of the seven seals, and I heard one of the four living creatures saying, as with a voice of thunder,</p>\n                  <p class=\"conversation\">\n                    “Come and see!”\n                  </p>\n                </li>\n                <li value=\"02\">And behold, a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">white horse</span>, and he who sat on it had a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">bow</span>. A <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">crown</span> was given to him, and he came forth conquering, and to conquer.</li>\n              </ol>\n            </blockquote>\n\n          <figure>\n            <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-280.webp 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-380.webp 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-480.webp 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-640.webp 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-840.webp 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1280.webp 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1600.webp 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-6-1\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the white horse”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the white horse”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"841\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-280.jpg 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-380.jpg 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-480.jpg 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-640.jpg 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-840.jpg 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1280.jpg 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1600.jpg 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/1er-cavalier-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the white horse”.<br>\n              <q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-6-1\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">And behold, a white horse, and he who sat on it had a bow. A crown was given to him, and he came forth conquering, and to conquer</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verse 2.</figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n\n\n          <h6 class=\"yellow\">second seal: the fiery red horse - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 3 to 4</h6>\n\n          <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-6-3\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-6-3\">\n            <ol class=\"doc\">\n              <li value=\"03\"><p>When he opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature saying,</p>\n                <p class=\"conversation\">\n                  “Come!”\n                </p>\n              </li>\n              <li value=\"04\">Another came forth, a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">red horse</span>. To him who sat on it was given power to take peace from the earth, and that they should kill one another. There was given to him a great <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">sword</span>.</li>\n            </ol>\n          </blockquote>\n\n          <figure>\n            <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-280.webp 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-380.webp 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-480.webp 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-640.webp 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-840.webp 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1280.webp 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1600.webp 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-6-3\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horsee feu”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horsee feu”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"776\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-280.jpg 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-380.jpg 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-480.jpg 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-640.jpg 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-840.jpg 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1280.jpg 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1600.jpg 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/2eme-cavalier-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the fiery red horse”.<br>\n            <q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-6-3\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">To him who sat on it was given power to take peace from the earth, and that they should kill one another. There was given to him a great sword</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 3 to 4.</figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n        \n\n          <h6 class=\"yellow\">third seal: the black horse - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 5 to 6</h6>\n\n          <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-6-5\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-6-5\">\n            <ol class=\"doc\">\n              <li value=\"05\">\n                <p>When he opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature saying,</p>\n                <p class=\"conversation\">\n                  “Come and see!”\n                </p>\n                <p>And behold, a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">black horse</span>, and he who sat on it had a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">balance</span> in his hand.</p>\n              </li>\n              <li value=\"06\">\n                <p>I heard a voice in the midst of the four living creatures saying,</p>\n                <p class=\"conversation\">\n                  “Achoenix of wheat for a denarius, and three choenix of barley for a denarius! Don't damage the oil and the wine!”\n                </p>\n              </li>\n            </ol>\n          </blockquote>\n\n          <figure>\n            <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-280.webp 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-380.webp 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-480.webp 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-640.webp 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-840.webp 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1280.webp 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1600.webp 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-6-5\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"817\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-280.jpg 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-380.jpg 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-480.jpg 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-640.jpg 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-840.jpg 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1280.jpg 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1600.jpg 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/3eme-cavalier-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-6-5\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">he who sat on it had a balance in his hand</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite> chapter 6 verse 5.</figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n        \n\n          <h6 class=\"yellow\">fourth seal: the greenish horse - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 7 to 8</h6>\n\n          <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-6-7\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-6-7\">\n            <ol class=\"doc\">\n              <li value=\"07\">\n                When he opened the fourth seal, I heard the fourth living creature saying,\n              <p class=\"conversation\">\n                “Come and see!”\n              </p>\n              </li>\n              <li value=\"08\">And behold, a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">pale horse</span>, and he who sat on it, his name was <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Death</span>. <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Hades</span> followed with him.</li>\n              <li>Authority over one fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword, with famine, with death, and by the wild animals of the earth was given to him.</li>\n            </ol>\n          </blockquote>\n\n          <figure>\n            <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-280.webp 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-380.webp 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-480.webp 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-640.webp 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-840.webp 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1280.webp 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1600.webp 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-6-7\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse, Death, Hades”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse, Death, Hades”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"253\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-280.jpg 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-380.jpg 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-480.jpg 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-640.jpg 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-840.jpg 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1280.jpg 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1600.jpg 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/4eme-cavalier-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “the black horse, Death”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-6-7\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">his name was Death. Hades followed with him</q>, <cite>The Revelation</cite> chapter 6 verse 8.</figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n        \n\n          <h6 class=\"yellow\">landscape around the four horsemen - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 14 to 17</h6>\n\n          <blockquote id=\"renvoi-apocalypse-6-14\" cite=\"https://francois-vidit.com/docs/en/bruges/hopital-saint-jean/saint-jean/page:20#apocalypse-6-14\">\n            <ol class=\"doc\">\n              <li value=\"14\">The sky was removed like a scroll when it is rolled up. Every mountain and island were moved out of their places.</li>\n              <li value=\"15\"><span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">The kings of the earth, the princes, the commanding officers, the rich, the strong, and every slave and free person, hid themselves in the caves and in the rocks of the mountains</span>.</li>\n              <li value=\"16\">\n                <p>They told the mountains and the rocks,</p>\n                <p class=\"conversation\">\n                  “Fall on us, and hide us from the face of him who sits on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb,\n                </p>\n              </li>\n              <li value=\"17\">\n                <p class=\"conversation\">\n                  for the great day of his wrath has come; and who is able to stand?”\n                </p>\n              </li>\n            </ol>\n          </blockquote>\n\n          <figure>\n            <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-280.webp 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-380.webp 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-480.webp 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-640.webp 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-840.webp 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1280.webp 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1600.webp 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-640.jpg\" id=\"image-apocalypse-6-14\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “landscape around the four horsemen”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the right inner shutter, “landscape around the four horsemen”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-80-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"484\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-280.jpg 280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-380.jpg 380w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-480.jpg 480w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-640.jpg 640w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-840.jpg 840w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1280.jpg 1280w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1600.jpg 1600w,\n            /docs/saint-jean/cavaliers-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the right inner shutter, “landscape around the four horsemen”.<br><q cite=\"#renvoi-apocalypse-6-14\" style=\"quotes:'«' '»';\">Every mountain and island were moved out of their places</q> - <cite>The Revelation</cite>, chapter 6 verses 14 to 17.</figcaption>\n          </figure>\n\n\n</article>"
}